post_text:
Math Night at CES: Can We Count You In?

We would like to invite you to Math Night: Can We Count You In? on Thursday, January 25th from 6:30-7:30! We will begin with an overview of the new Bridges program for grades K-5. This overview will provide parents some information about skills and strategies they can expect their students to learn over the course of their time here at CES. Following the overview, there will be games and manipulatives set up and more specific information about the math expectations of your child's grade level. The night will end with some light refreshments and questions from you! We hope you will join us!

Please RSVP to let us know if you will be joining us!

post_text: Attention, all families past and present of Chaplin Elementary School: On November 1, 1992 (25 years!), the students and staff of Chaplin Elementary school buried a time capsule to be opened on November 1, 2017. We are looking for former students and families of CES to join us for this historic event. Please share this post. Contact interested parties who may not be on FB. Do you know someone who attended CES in 1992? Let them know. Guests will watch as the time capsule is removed. The time capsule's content will then be displayed in the gym for all to see. Refreshments will be provided by the PTO. Post any questions here.

post_text:
Thanks to the efforts of parents, students, teachers and community volunteers, we got the new plastic up on the greenhouse. What a fabulous team! The pots in the greenhouse have been emptied, stacked & put away in the potting room; The garden beds were weeded and have a new layer of compost soil from the our compost bin; gutters are filled with soil, waiting for the baby lettuce we will grow for the cafeteria, and most of all - the greenhouse has a new double layer of clear plastic battened down and snug for winter.
We owe a great deal of thanks to Jeff & Karen Woodward for leading the group in putting up the plastic. Please see the attached picture, courtesy of Kellie Monroe.

Thank you everyone!

Mrs. Dufresne

post_text: Join us tonight at Parish Hill High School at 6:00 p.m. for the "Trunk-and-Treat" followed by the movie "Hotel Transylvania 2."
text: Join us tonight at Parish Hill High School at 6:00 p.m. for the "Trunk-and-Treat" followed by the movie "Hotel Transylvania 2."

post_text:
The Parish Hill Middle/High School PTO is partnering with the Middle School Council to have a ‘trunk and treat” for the community’s small children prior to the start of the movie, “Hotel Transylvania 2” on Friday, October 21st at Parish Hill. All are welcome to join!

The “trunk and treat” starts at 6:00 pm in the Parish Hill Middle/High School’s parking lot.

The movie will start at 6:30 pm.

There is no admission cost for the movie, but refreshments including chips, cookies, popcorn, ice pops, juice, cookies and gummies will be sold at $1.00 each. Please come and support the PTO and the Middle School Council.

post_text: Join us tomorrow evening at 6:00 P.M. in the Library for a presentation by award-winning author Melissa Stewart! Melissa has written over 150 science books for children, and is excited to speak to our community about her books and the beauty and wonder of the natural world.

post_text:
Spirit Week for Family Literacy
October 17-21

Monday, October 17th - "Wear Something You Can Read" Day
Join us for Family Night With Author Melissa Stewart from 6-7 p.m. in the gym. The Scholastic Book Fair will be open in the library. Melissa Stewart's books will also be available to purchase.

Tuesday, October 18th - "Read with Crazy Hair and Clothes" Day
During the day, each grade level will attend a presentation by our guest author, Melissa Stewart, as well as reading with their crazy hair and clothes.

Wednesday, October 19th - "Dress as a Book Character" Day

Thursday, October 20th - "Read a new book to a Stuffed Animal Day." Students will have an opportunity to choose a new free book, thanks to Scholastic's "Bruised Books" program. (Guidelines: One "stuffy" per student, all animals have to follow school rules, and the animal has to fit into your backpack)

Friday, October 21st - "Read-In" Day - "Wear Comfy Clothing or Pajamas" (and find a great place to "read-in") Day.
